SIMPLE: caster
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Caster
<hw>Cast"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
casts; <as>as, <ex>caster</ex> of stones, etc.</as> ; a
<xex>caster</xex> of cannon; a <xex>caster</xex> of accounts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vial, cruet, or other small vessel, used to
contain condiments at the table; <as>as, a set of
<ex>casters</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A stand to hold a set of cruets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A small wheel on a swivel, on which furniture is
supported and moved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castigate</ent>⟦br⟧
